RACE.RACE_TEXT: DEL MAR RACE 1 1M Dirt CR: 68. Maiden Claiming Purse 22000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $20,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: VULIN raced up close in the two path early, bid outside the pacesetter at the half-mile pole, dueled leaving the backstretch, put away inner rival and moved over to the rail while fighting with FAST INVESTMENT on the far turn, shook free from that foe at the quarter pole, kept to task through the lane and held safely. BOGINSKAYA settled well off the rail then angled down to the two path on the first turn, gave chased two wide then along the rail into the lane, moved out in the drive and chased willingly through the final furlong but could not reach the winner. FAST INVESTMENT stalked four then three wide on the first turn, bid three deep in the middle stages, dueled outside VULIN on the far turn, could not kick on with that rival at the quarter pole, chased two wide into the drive, flattened in the furlong grounds but churned on to secure the show. BEST YEAR EVER bobbled and took up shortly after the start, trailed five wide around the first turn, moved into range then put in a mild bid four deep on the backstretch, failed to sustain the challenge and chased the top pair four wide into the stretch before weakining. ROUND IN CIRCLES stepped to the front from inside, pressure by outer rivals midway up the backstretch, lost command approaching the far turn, dropped back around that bend and weakened.

ENTRY.COMMENT: up close 2path, bid outside 1/2, dueled, cleared 1/4, held safely

RACE.FOOTNOTES: MAN O ROSE coaxed clear and moved into the two path, took pressure from outside, cleared at the quarter pole and held well through the final furlong. RHYTHEM ON STAGE was off a bit slow to begin, moved inside racing at the back, saved ground through the turn, then rallied to edge ANTONSEN for second. ANTONSEN chased two wide into the turn, eased out around the turn and spun four wide into the lane, finished determinedly from outside but got outkicked for the place honors. MORE TRY got put in tight inside the leader early and took hold, moved into the two path on the turn, tipped three wide into the lane and finished evenly. GRAND TIGER chased off the rail then bid outside leaving the backstretch, chased the winner past the quarter pole and weakened.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: MIXTO stepped to the front and showed the way early from inside, took pressure up the backstretch, dueled around the far turn, lost command in upper stretch, battled back along the fence and edged BAD SNEAKERS in the closing moments. BAD SNEAKERS brushed with inner rival at the start, was prominent early in the two path, moved up to pressure the leader in the middle stages, dueled around the second bend, took over in upper stretch, fought head to head with MIXTO in the late stages and was overtaken nearing the wire. EXCEL CALCULATOR broke a step slow, stalked from the rail, roused on the far turn, chased a bit off the rail into the lane, tipped out in the drive, could not summon the needed late kick but stayed on to hold the show. MAUNA KEA BOUND chased in the four path early, went two wide into the far turn, angled out and came four wide into the drive and lacked the needed response. PIONEER PRINCE stalked three deep through both turns and weakened when called upon. SHIP AND SCAM broke a step slow and brushed with outer rival, tracked in the two path, along the rail into second bend, angled out with a quarter mile left to run, spun five wide into the lane and had little left for the drive.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: IMMELMANN hustled clear from outside, crossed over, set all the pace to the stretch, roused and put to left then right handed urging and held well. SHADY TIGER chased two wide outside a rival, moved out in the lane, finished willingly but needed more to overtake the winner late. CURLIN'S KAOS off slow to begin, raced a bit greenly early and dove down to the inside trailing the field, tipped out past the quarter pole, produced a mild rally and gained the show. CLEMENTS RIDE traveled near the back on the inside into the turn, saved ground through the bend, angled out in upper stretch and offered a mild response to round out the superfecta. ANNAN coaxed from the gate, forwardly placed early while racing greenly on the inside, asked left handed into the lane and weakened. JETFIRE chased three deep then angled in at the seven-sixteenths pole, saved ground to the stretch and weakened. MONSIEUR took up early when JETFIRE cut over at the seven-sixteenths pole, chased two to three wide around the bend and lacked a rally. PRINCE PRANCEALOT broke a step slow, traveled near the back outside a rival into the turn, trailed into the stretch and failed to menace.
